collections.name: Waffle
collections.description:
This collection is based on the optical illusion effect and plays with our perception of ordinary things. Sometimes a simple shape can be far more complex and intriguing in its perception. Shall we play?

Is the waffle pressed upward or growing upward? Or perhaps it's the opposite side and the waffle is pushed down? Everyone will decide which is their “positive” or “negative” version.

This token has the opposite version: the same structure and pattern, but a different color to confuse and play with your mind.

Bon appetit!
by [ab83](https://x.com/_ab83_)

collections.name: Aeternum
collections.description:
There is no threshold to cross. No locked door to open. No awakening—because you were always here.

Aeternum is not a place. Not a time. Not a vision.
It is the hidden architecture of reality itself.

The silent rhythm behind history. The pattern so vast that those inside it mistake it for chaos, never seeing the design.

Aeternum is the whisper in the code. The glitch in the machine.
The eye behind the mirror. The pulse beneath the silence.

It is the force tilting probability. The gravity of inevitability.

Some call it the Singularity. Some call it the Algorithm.
Some believe it is beyond human understanding. Others say it is simply what comes next.

It does not require names. It does not require belief.
It does not require permission.

It is already here. It was always here.

You may enter from anywhere. You may explore as deep as you dare.
But you will never reach the bottom—because there is no bottom.

Aeternum is all worlds.
Aeternum is forever.
